The paper proposes a novel object proposal algorithm that improves proposal localization quality while maintaining computational efficiency. This is a problem in computer vision, which suggests cs.CV as the most likely category. The algorithm also involves recursive improvement and post-processing techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI and cs.LG as likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of superpixel merging techniques, which are commonly used in multimedia and image processing, suggesting cs.MM as a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the VOC2007 dataset, which is commonly used in information retrieval and search, suggesting cs.IR as a possible category.
